                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-718" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN EATON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable S</hi> 193.) At half-past two o'clock, on the 10th of July, I was in plain clothes in the City-road—there was a procession of the Old Friends—I saw the prisoner and another trying a great many pockets—the prisoner put his hand into a man's pocket, took out this hand<lb></lb>kerchief, and put it under his jacket—I laid hold of him, and he was very violent—in going to the station he dropped these four other handkerchiefs.</p>
